'''Malo Arthur Gusto''' (born 19 May 2003) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for {{English football updater|Chelsea}} club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].<ref name=":13" /><ref name=":5" />

Originally a product of the [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] [[Olympique Lyonnais Reserves and Academy|academy]], Gusto entered the Lyon first team in 2021, where he made over 50 league appearances. During the January 2023 transfer window, Gusto moved to Chelsea for a reported €30 million fee.

Internationally, Gusto has played for France at both youth and senior levels.

==Early life==
Malo Arthur Gusto<ref name=":13">{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/3681595 |title=2023/24 Premier League squad lists |publisher=Premier League |date=13 September 2023 |access-date=6 October 2023}}</ref> was born on 19 May 2003<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/player/bio/_/id/308947/malo-gusto |title=Malo Gusto Biography |publisher=ESPN |access-date=26 December 2023}}</ref> in [[Décines-Charpieu]], a commune in the Metropolis of Lyon.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur83189.html |title=Malo Gusto |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=6 October 2023}}</ref> Growing up in [[Villefontaine]], Isère, his father first made him play [[rugby football|rugby]], but the young Gusto soon chose to play association football, pursuing his dream to become a professional footballer while studying for a [[baccalauréat technologique]].<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|date=17 December 2020|title=Un jeune Nord-Isérois passe pro avec l'OL|url=https://www.ledauphine.com/sport/2020/12/17/un-jeune-nord-iserois-passe-pro-avec-l-ol|access-date=2021-10-22|website=[[Le Dauphiné libéré]]|language=FR-fr}}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite web|last=[[Agence France-Presse]]|date=22 September 2021|title=18 ans, formé à Lyon... l'Isérois Malo Gusto sur orbite|url=https://www.ledauphine.com/sport/2021/09/22/18-ans-forme-a-lyon-malo-gusto-sur-orbite|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[Le Dauphiné libéré]]|language=FR-fr}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Lyon===
[[File:Olympique lyonnais - ES Troyes AC L1 19-08-2022 - Malo Gusto.jpg|thumb|upright|Gusto with [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] in 2022]]

Malo Gusto started playing at the [[Villefontaine#Sports|ASVF]],<ref>{{Cite web|title=ASVF Football : Malo Gusto|url=https://asvffootball.sportsregions.fr/saison-2019-2020/actualites-du-club/asvf-football--malo-gusto-813949|access-date=2021-10-22|website=asvffootball.sportsregions.fr|language=fr|archive-date=26 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211026045432/https://asvffootball.sportsregions.fr/saison-2019-2020/actualites-du-club/asvf-football--malo-gusto-813949|url-status=dead}}</ref> later joining [[FC Bourgoin-Jallieu|Bourgoin-Jallieu]] on a one-year spell,<ref>{{Cite web|date=22 December 2020|title=Malo Gusto signe un contrat pro – fcbourgoinjallieu|url=https://fcbourgoinjallieu.com/malo-gusto-signe-un-contrat-pro/|access-date=2021-10-22|website=fcbourgoinjallieu.com|language=fr-FR}}</ref> before entering the Lyon academy as an under-14, in a move resembling the one of his elder academy fellow [[Amine Gouiri]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|last=Cornu|first=Adrien|date=30 September 2021|title=Malo Gusto, le couloir lui revient de droit|url=https://madeinfoot.ouest-france.fr/infos/article-ol-malo-gusto-le-couloir-lui-revient-de-droit-355998.html|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211023204323/https://madeinfoot.ouest-france.fr/infos/article-ol-malo-gusto-le-couloir-lui-revient-de-droit-355998.html|archive-date=2021-10-23|access-date=22 October 2021|website=[[Ouest-France]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|date=17 December 2020|title=OL: Malo Gusto, 5e joueur de l'Académie à signer pro en 2020|url=https://www.leprogres.fr/sport/2020/12/17/ol-malo-gusto-5e-joueur-de-l-academie-a-signer-pro-en-2020|access-date=2021-10-22|website=[[Le Progrès]]|language=FR-fr}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|last=Leplang|first=Geoffrey|date=13 January 2021|title=Malo Gusto, le Gone prêt à rugir de plaisir • Actufoot • Actu du foot pro/amateur|url=https://www.actufoot.com/malo-gusto-le-gone-pret-a-rugir-de-plaisir|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211022152831/https://www.actufoot.com/malo-gusto-le-gone-pret-a-rugir-de-plaisir|archive-date=2021-10-22|access-date=2021-10-22|website={{ill|Actufoot|fr}}|language=fr}}</ref><ref name=":4" /> Gusto so happened to arrive in [[Lyon]] the same year that the club moved to the [[Parc Olympique Lyonnais|Stade des Lumières]], in his home town.<ref name=":3" />

There he was part of the same generation as [[Florent da Silva]], [[Yaya Soumaré]] and [[Rayan Cherki]], eventually signing his first professional contract with the French club in December 2020.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=17 December 2020 |title=Malo Gusto signe son premier contrat professionnel |url=https://www.ol.fr/fr/actualites/malo-gusto-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel-1 |access-date=2021-10-22 |website=OL.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref name=":7">{{Cite web |title=Premier contrat professionnel pour Malo Gusto à l'OL |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Premier-contrat-professionnel-pour-malo-gusto-a-l-ol/1206853 |access-date=2024-03-10 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> At that point he had already made a few appearance on the team sheet for [[2020–21 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] games under [[Rudi Garcia]]'s management, while already having shown his talent in the [[2019–20 UEFA Youth League|Youth League]] and [[2020–21 Championnat National 2|National 2]], with the [[Olympique Lyonnais II|reserve]].<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":0" />

Malo Gusto made his professional debut for [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] on 24 January 2021, replacing [[Bruno Guimarães]] on the 90th minute of a 5–0 [[2020–21 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] away win against their [[Olympique Lyonnais–AS Saint-Étienne rivalry|Derby du Rhône]] rivals of [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]].<ref name=":6" /><ref>{{Cite web|last1=Joret|first1=Nicolas|last2=Rego|first2=Raul|date=24 January 2021|title=Résultat et résumé Saint-Étienne – Lyon, Ligue 1 Uber Eats, 21e journée|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-1/2020-2021/asse-ol-live/477364|access-date=2021-01-24|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr}}</ref> Having made another short Ligue 1 appearance at the end of the [[2020–21 Olympique Lyonnais season|season]], the young defender signed a new contract with Lyon in June, tying him to the club until 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|date=4 June 2021|title=OL: le jeune Malo Gusto prolonge pour une saison supplémentaire|url=https://www.leprogres.fr/sport/2021/06/04/ol-le-jeune-malo-gusto-prolonge-pour-une-saison-supplementaire|access-date=2021-10-22|website=[[Le Progrès]]|language=FR-fr}}</ref><ref name=":8">{{Cite web |date=4 June 2021 |title=L'OL prolonge Malo Gusto |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/L-ol-prolonge-malo-gusto/1259080 |access-date=2021-10-23 |website=[[L'Équipe]] |language=fr}}</ref>

Gusto started his first game during Lyon's opening match against [[Stade Brestois 29|Brest]] on 7 August.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|last=Penot|first=Hervé|date=14 September 2020|title=OL : Malo Gusto, le (jeune) latéral qui brûle les étapes|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Ol-malo-gusto-le-jeune-lateral-qui-brule-les-etapes/1285298|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr}}</ref> By doing so he became the youngest defender to start a [[2021–22 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] game for OL since [[Samuel Umtiti]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Chorlet|first=Fabien|date=11 August 2021|title=OL, FC Barcelone : un Lyonnais s'offre un record de Samuel Umtiti|url=https://www.butfootballclub.fr/ol/actualite/ol-fc-barcelone-un-lyonnais-s-offre-un-record-de-samuel-umtiti-661921|access-date=2021-10-23|website={{ill|But !|fr}}|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Berthilier|first=Thomas|date=11 August 2021|title=OL : Malo Gusto plus jeune défenseur titulaire depuis Samuel Umtiti|url=https://www.olympique-et-lyonnais.com/ol-malo-gusto-plus-jeune-defenseur-titulaire-depuis-samuel-umtiti,226713.html|access-date=2021-10-23|website=Olympique & Lyonnais|language=fr-FR}}</ref>

While still appearing to be behind [[Léo Dubois]] in the right back hierarchy, Gusto still took the spotlight on several occasions under Bosz's direction, as he started games such as the 2–0 [[2021–22 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] away win against [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] or the 2–1 [[2021–22 Ligue 1|Ligue 1]] away loss against [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":6" /><ref>{{Cite web|last1=Pereira|first1=Alexis|last2=Léger-Moëc|first2=Aurélien|date=20 September 2021|title=Malo Gusto s'est mis tout l'OL dans la poche|url=https://www.footmercato.net/a637694210348570566-malo-gusto-sest-mis-tout-lol-dans-la-poche|access-date=2021-10-23|website={{ill|Foot Mercato|fr}}|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Parbaud|first=Corentin|date=20 September 2021|title=OL: Rothen sous le charme de Gusto, "un gamin pétri de talent"|url=https://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/ligue-1/ol-rothen-sous-le-charme-de-gusto-apres-son-match-contre-le-psg_AV-202109210468.html|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[RMC Sport]]|language=fr}}</ref>

===Chelsea===
On 29 January 2023, Chelsea announced the signing of Malo Gusto on a deal until 2030.<ref name=":5" /> Lyon reported the transfer fee to be €30 million plus €5 million in bonuses.<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 January 2023 |title=TRANSFERT DE MALO GUSTO À CHELSEA…EN PRÊT À L'OL JUSQU'AU 30 JUIN 2023 |url=https://www.ol.fr/fr/actualites/transfert-de-malo-gusto-a-chelsea-prete-a-l-ol-jusqu-au-30-juin-2023 |access-date=2024-03-10 |website=ol.fr}}</ref> He was loaned back to Lyon until the end of the [[2022–23 Olympique Lyonnais season|2022–23]] season.<ref name=":5">{{cite web|url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/gusto-signs-for-chelsea|publisher=Chelsea F.C.|title=Gusto signs for Chelsea|date=29 January 2023|accessdate=29 January 2023}}</ref> On 13 August, he made his debut for the club in a 1–1 draw against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in Chelsea's opening match of the [[2023–24 Chelsea F.C. season|2023–24]] season.<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12937533/chelsea-1-1-liverpool-mauricio-pochettinos-side-fight-back-to-draw-his-first-premier-league-game-in-charge|title=Chelsea 1–1 Liverpool: Mauricio Pochettino's side fight back to draw his first Premier League game in charge|work=Sky Sports |date=13 August 2023|accessdate=14 August 2023}}</ref> On 24 September, he was shown his first [[Red card (association football)|red card]] in his career after [[Jarred Gillett]] went to the [[Video assistant referee|VAR]] monitor to review a late challenge he made on [[Lucas Digne]] in their home defeat to [[Aston Villa F.C|Aston Villa]].<ref>{{Cite web| last=Beardmore|first=Michael|date=24 September 2023|title=Chelsea 0–1 Aston Villa| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66835404|access-date=13 February 2024| website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

The 2024–25 season saw Gusto deployed, alongside [[Reece James]], as a [[midfielder]] as well as a full-back.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Maresca pleased with the versatility of Gusto and James |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/maresca-pleased-with-the-versatility-of-gusto-and-james |access-date=2025-12-16 |website=www.chelseafc.com |language=en-gb}}</ref> On 8 November 2025, Gusto scored his first goal for Chelsea against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], ending a run of 165 games without a goal.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Kinsella |first=Nizaar |date=2025-11-09 |title=Chelsea 3-0 Wolves: Analysis of Malo Gusto's goal |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cwy1247yd8jo |access-date=2025-11-09 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Gusto also scored and assisted [[Cole Palmer]] in a 2–0 victory over [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] on 13 December.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lovell |first=Clare |date=13 December 2025 |title=Chelsea return to top four with 2-0 home win over Everton |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/chelsea-return-top-four-with-2-0-win-over-everton-2025-12-13/ |access-date=15 December 2025 |work=[[Reuters]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Gusto is of Portuguese descent through his father,<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/ONE-TO-WATCH/2021/09/21/one-to-watch-malo-gusto-lyon-s-young-lion-bosz-neymar | title=One to watch: Malo Gusto, Lyon's young lion | work=Ligue1 COM }}</ref> and Martiniquais descent through his mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onzemondial.com/ligue-1/exclu-malo-gusto-je-ne-suis-pas-un-joueur-qui-doute-778283|title=EXCLU – Malo Gusto : " Je ne suis pas un joueur qui doute "|date=17 May 2022|website=Onze Mondial}}</ref> He is a youth international for France: he first played as a [[midfielder]] for the [[France national under-16 football team|under-16]], but was later selected as a [[Fullback (association football)|fullback]] with the [[France national under-17 football team|U17]] and [[France national under-18 football team|U18]]. However, he did not play any official game with the latter, as the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Europe|COVID-19 pandemic]] did not allow most youth international encounters or competitions to go on as planned during 2020–2021.<ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite web|date=12 November 2020|title=Malo Gusto, le prochain gone à intégrer l'équipe première ?|url=https://cafecremesport.com/2020/11/12/malo-gusto-le-prochain-gone-a-integrer-lequipe-premiere/|website=Café Crème Sport}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Malo Gusto profile|url=https://www.fff.fr/equipe-nationale/joueur/8378-gusto-malo/fiche.html|access-date=2021-10-22|website=[[Fédération Française de Football]]}}</ref>

In September 2021, as the pandemic was slowing down, the young defender eventually gained his next French cap, this time playing with the [[France national under-19 football team|under-19]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":6" /> He was called up for a friendly tournament in [[Slovenia]], against [[Russia national under-19 football team|Russia]], [[Slovakia national under-19 football team|Slovakia]] and the [[Slovenia national under-19 football team|hosts]], along with his teammate [[Rayan Cherki]].<ref name=":12">{{Cite web|last=Poyade|first=Loïc|date=27 August 2021|title=Equipe de France U19 : La liste des Bleuets pour le tournoi en Slovénie|url=https://madeinfoot.ouest-france.fr/infos/article-equipe-de-france-u19-la-liste-des-bleuets-pour-le-tournoi-en-slovenie-352874.html|access-date=22 October 2021|website=[[Ouest-France]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Orsini|first=Vincent|date=26 August 2021|title=Un tournoi amical en Slovénie au menu|url=https://www.fff.fr/article/3285-un-tournoi-amical-en-slovenie-au-menu.html|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[Fédération Française de Football|FFF]]}}</ref> There he started and played every minute of all three games, even ending up wearing the captain's armband.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2 September 2021|title=Portée par un grand Rayan Cherki, l'équipe de France U19 domine la Russie|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Portee-par-un-grand-rayan-cherki-l-equipe-de-france-u19-domine-la-russie/1282590|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=3 September 2021|title=Sélections : Des Lyonnais ont brillé|url=https://www.ol.fr/fr-fr/contenus/articles/2021/09/03/selections-des-lyonnais-ont-brille|access-date=2021-10-23|website=OL.fr|language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Orsini|first=Vincent|date=4 September 2021|title=Match nul (1–1) contre la Slovaquie|url=https://www.fff.fr/article/3364-match-nul-1-1-contre-la-slovaquie.html|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[Fédération Française de Football|FFF]]}}</ref>

However only a month later both he and Cherki were directly promoted to the [[France national under-21 football team|under-21 team]], by [[Sylvain Ripoll]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=30 September 2021|title=Malo Gusto, Amine Adli, Rayan Cherki et Janis Antiste convoqués avec les Espoirs|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Malo-gusto-amine-adli-rayan-cherki-et-janis-antiste-convoques-avec-les-espoirs/1289059|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=[[Agence France-Presse]]|date=30 September 2021|title=Le Berjallien Malo Gusto (OL) appelé pour la première fois chez les Espoirs !|url=https://www.ledauphine.com/sport/2021/09/30/le-berjallien-malo-gusto-(ol)-appele-pour-la-premiere-fois-chez-les-espoirs|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[Le Dauphiné libéré]]|language=FR-fr}}</ref> The two of them made their debut coming off the bench with the ''espoirs'' on 8 October 2021, helping their team to an important 5–0 win against [[Ukraine national under-21 football team|Ukraine]] in the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|Euro]] [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group H|qualifying]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=[[Agence France-Presse]]|date=8 October 2021|title=Football. Espoirs : la créativité de Cherki pour réparer l'accroc des Féroé|url=https://www.ledauphine.com/sport/2021/10/08/espoirs-la-creativite-de-cherki-pour-reparer-l-accroc-des-feroe|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[Le Dauphiné libéré]]|language=FR-fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Mayen|first=Philippe|date=8 October 2021|title=Les Bleuets plein gaz (5–0)|url=https://www.fff.fr/article/3590-les-bleuets-plein-gaz-5-0-.html|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[Fédération Française de Football|FFF]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Cailloux|first=Thibaut|date=8 October 2021|title=Résultat et résumé France Espoirs – Ukraine Espoirs, Qualif. Euro Espoirs, 4e journée Gr. H|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/qualif-euro-espoirs/2023/france-espoirs-ukraine-espoirs-live/513501|access-date=2021-10-23|website=[[L'Équipe]]|language=fr}}</ref>

On 9 October 2023, Gusto received his first call-up to the [[France national football team|France national team]] for matches against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] and [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]], replacing the injured [[Jules Koundé]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gusto on maiden call-up, James competition and inspirational Thiago Silva |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/gusto-on-maiden-call-up-james-thiago-silva |access-date=2024-03-10 |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Deux changements dans la liste des 23 |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/11105-deux-changements-dans-la-liste-des-23.html |access-date=2024-03-10 |website=fff.fr}}</ref> On 13 October 2023, he made his international debut in the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|European Championship qualifier]] match against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]], coming off the bench in the 80th minute, helping France to a 2–1 victory, clinching the qualification as a result.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 October 2023 |title=Winning debuts for Colwill and Gusto as two qualify for Euros |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/winning-debuts-for-colwill-and-gusto-as-two-qualify-for-euros |access-date=2024-03-10 |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |language=en}}</ref>

Gusto was selected as a member of the France squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Tolisso misses out on 2026 World Cup as Gusto, Cherki and Barcola selected |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/tolisso-misses-out-on-2026-world-cup-as-gusto-cherki-and-barcola-selected-42872270 |access-date=2026-05-30 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Gusto is seen as an agile and offensively minded player, ever since playing eight-a-side football at Villefontaine, and he first played as an [[attacking midfielder]] or a [[Forward (association football)|forward]]. While he was at the [[Olympique Lyonnais Reserves and Academy|Lyon academy]] he played in several different positions, including [[wide midfielder]], [[advanced playmaker]], and [[right winger]]. He eventually settled as a [[right back]], where he took full advantage of his speed and athleticism.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":3" /><ref name=":6" /><ref name=":9">{{Cite web |last=Monegier |first=Tom |date=18 July 2021 |title=Malo Gusto, le latéral droit qui monte à l'OL |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a1247685717625159587-malo-gusto-le-lateral-droit-qui-monte-a-lol |access-date=2021-10-23 |website={{ill|Foot Mercato|fr}} |language=fr}}</ref><ref name=":10">{{Cite web |last=Guillemet |first=Hugo |date=19 July 2021 |title=Avec Gusto et Lukeba, l'OL joue la carte jeunes |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Avec-gusto-et-lukeba-l-ol-joue-la-carte-jeunes/1271476 |access-date=2021-10-23 |website=[[L'Équipe]] |language=fr}}</ref><ref name=":11">{{Cite web |last=Ouggourni |first=Pierre-Hakim |date=5 August 2021 |title=De Gusto à Ugochukwu, cinq jeunes joueurs à suivre cette saison |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/ligue-1/ligue-1-de-gusto-a-ugochukwu-cinq-jeunes-joueurs-a-suivre-cette-saison-db15f32e-f370-11eb-ae59-20d6564a0c37 |access-date=23 October 2021 |website=[[Ouest-France]] |language=fr}}</ref>

